  "title": "Software Support Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform comprehensive troubleshooting to diagnose and fix issues related to software configuration, performance, and integration.</li>\n  <li>Identify, analyze, and resolve coding bugs in a timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Review and update app configurations to ensure optimal performance and compatibility.</li>\n  <li>Assist in resolving integration issues with other systems and platforms.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical support to customers and address their concerns effectively.</li>\n  <li>Maintain detailed documentation of issues, solutions, and best practices.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with development, QA, and support teams to ensure seamless software operation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>2-5 years of relevant professional working experience.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in software development and bug fixing.</li>\n  <li>Strong troubleshooting skills with the ability to diagnose and resolve complex issues.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with software configuration management and performance monitoring tools.</li>\n  <li>Experience with <strong>Node.js, React, Kafka, Keycloak, MQTT, Microservices, Docker, Kubernetes, Podman, MongoDB, and IBM MQ.</strong></li>\n  <li>Available for 24/7 standby and open to working overtime or in shift roles as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
